

What is the Proxy Design Pattern?
..................................................................
The Proxy Pattern is a Structural Design Pattern that provides a placeholder (proxy) object to control access to another object.

Definition: A Proxy object acts as an intermediary between the client and the real object. It can add security, logging, caching, lazy loading, or access control without modifying the original object.
..................................................................
Real-Time Banking Example
..................................................................
Suppose only Admin users are allowed to approve loans.

Instead of allowing direct access to the LoanService, all requests go through a Proxy.

Customer

      │

      ▼

LoanServiceProxy

      │

      ▼

LoanService

The proxy checks whether the user is an Admin before forwarding the request.

Step 1: Subject Interface
..................................................................
public interface LoanService {

    void approveLoan();
}
Step 2: Real Subject
..................................................................
public class RealLoanService implements LoanService {

    @Override
    public void approveLoan() {

        System.out.println("Loan Approved");
    }
}
Step 3: Proxy Class
..................................................................
public class LoanServiceProxy implements LoanService {

    private RealLoanService realService = new RealLoanService();

    private String role;

    public LoanServiceProxy(String role) {

        this.role = role;
    }

    @Override
    public void approveLoan() {

        if ("ADMIN".equals(role)) {

            realService.approveLoan();

        } else {

            System.out.println("Access Denied");
        }
    }
}
Step 4: Client
..................................................................
public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        LoanService admin =
                new LoanServiceProxy("ADMIN");

        admin.approveLoan();

        LoanService customer =
                new LoanServiceProxy("CUSTOMER");

        customer.approveLoan();
    }
}
