Types of Proxy
1. Virtual Proxy
..................................................................
Creates an object only when it is needed (lazy loading).

Example:

Large Image

↓

Load only when user opens it
2. Protection Proxy
..................................................................
Controls access based on permissions.

Example:

Customer → View Account

Admin → Delete Account
3. Remote Proxy

Represents an object located on another server.

Example:

Client

↓

Remote Proxy

↓

Payment Service (Remote Server)

4. Caching Proxy
..................................................................
Stores previously fetched results to avoid repeated operations.

Example:

Customer Request

↓

Cache

↓

Database

If the data is already in the cache, the database is not called again.

Spring Boot Example

Suppose every transaction should be logged.

Instead of modifying the service:

transactionService.transfer();

Use a proxy:

proxy.transfer();

The proxy can:

Log the request
Check permissions
Validate input
Call the real service
